{"version":1,"entries":{"person_2874193_translations":{"at":1772689426024,"data":{"id":2874193,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Jane Methika Jiranorraphat, or Janeyeh, is a Thai-Taiwanese actor born to a Taiwanese father and Thai mother in Bangkok, Thailand. One of her two sisters, Pemika Jiranorraphat, is a model. Growing up, Jane attended Thai international schools and, in grade four, she attended school in Taiwan to practise her Chinese. In 2020, she graduated in Brand Communication from Bangkok University's Faculty of Communication Arts.  Before fully entering the industry, Jane competed in \"Miss Teen Thailand 2014\" and auditioned for JYP and YG in hopes of making it as a K-Pop idol. In 2015, she made her acting debut in the series \"Love Sick Season 2\".  Jane was previously a member of the project girl group SIZZY (formerly SISSY) formed by GMMTV in 2019. In 2023, they signed with Riser Music although they never released music under the label, ultimately disbanding on October 16, 2024, following the expiration of Jane's contract with GMMTV.","name":"Methika Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"รมิดา จีรนรภัทร","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ramida Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"MX","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ramida Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ramida Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"ラミダー・ジーラノラパット","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ID","iso_639_1":"id","name":"Bahasa indonesia","english_name":"Indonesian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ramida Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"VN","iso_639_1":"vi","name":"Tiếng Việt","english_name":"Vietnamese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ramida Jiranorraphat","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"拉米妲·吉勒诺拉帕","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"拉米妲·吉勒諾拉帕","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}}]}},"person_2098555_translations":{"at":1772689426687,"data":{"id":2098555,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Perth Tanapon Sukumpantanasan is a Thai actor and singer born in Bangkok. He graduated from Saint Dominic School and is currently a student at Srinakharinwirot University (SWU), majoring in Innovative Media Arts and Acting and Director Training.\n\nPerth made his acting debut as Breeze in the 2017 series \"Please... Seiyng Reiyk Wiyyan\". He rose to prominence portraying Ae in the series \"Love by chance\".\n\nHe was part of the boy band \"Tempt\" which disbanded in 2020. He was one of the artists in a ten-member boy band \"Boyfriends.\" Season 1 partnered with Ritz. Their first single is titled \"อาการงี้ (Hello Doctor)\".\n\nTanapon left his management AttractorTH along with Plan Rathavit and Gun Napat on July 13th, 2020. Worked as a freelancer. On April 4th, 2022 GMMTV announced on their social media platforms that Perth had joined the company as one of their artists.","name":"Tanapon Sukumpantanasan","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"ธนพนธ์ สุขุมพันธนาสาร","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"タナポン・スクムパンタナーサーン","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"Tanapon Sukumpantanasan, conhecido mundialmente como Perth, é um dos atores mais influentes da indústria BL tailandesa, agenciado pela GMMTV. Ele iniciou sua carreira com um estrondo em 2018, ao protagonizar o fenômeno global \"Love by Chance\", onde sua interpretação como Ae o transformou em uma estrela internacional aos 17 anos.\n\nApós um período como freelancer e passagens pelas bandas TEMPT e Boyfriends, Perth assinou com a GMMTV em 2022. Na agência, protagonizou a série \"Dangerous Romance\" (2023). Em 2024, iniciou uma nova e bem-sucedida fase em sua carreira ao ser escalado como o protagonista Yark-Fah em \"Perfect 10 Liners\", projeto que marcou o início de sua parceria oficial com Santa Pongsapak. Além da atuação, Perth é cantor sob o selo Riser Music e estuda Direção e Atuação na Universidade Srinakharinwirot (SWU).","name":"Perth Tanapon Sukumpantanasan","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"塔纳朋·苏库潘塔纳汕（ธนพนธ์ สุขุมพันธนาสาร），艺名Perth，2001年3月20日出生于泰国曼谷，泰籍华裔男演员、歌手，男子乐队TEMPT成员，毕业于诗纳卡宁威洛大学社会传播创新学院电影与数字媒体专业，主修表演与导演。\n\n2017年通过悬疑剧《please灵魂之声》出道。2018年因主演同性校园剧《不期而爱》崭露头角，随后出演《不期而爱2》《危险罗曼史》等作品。2019年客串出演《待到重逢时》《我的秘密新娘》等剧集。2022年签约GMMTV后，主演《我的足球教练》《骨肉相残》等剧集。2024年主演同性爱情剧《男神编码》，2025年参演《良师男友》。","name":"王俊勇","primary":false}}]}},"movie_1601195_keywords":{"at":1772689440866,"data":{"id":1601195,"keywords":[{"id":3485,"name":"comedian"},{"id":9716,"name":"stand-up comedy"}]}},"person_4829074_translations":{"at":1772689440937,"data":{"id":4829074,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Shino Shinozaki","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Сино Синодзаки","primary":false}},{"iso_3166